00:13:34,625 --> 00:13:37,791
After I met Fubuki, I decided
it was wrong to kill them.

259
00:13:39,500 --> 00:13:42,000
But that's also against
our orders.

260
00:13:43,875 --> 00:13:45,166
[chuckles]
In fact,

261
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:46,958
I'll probably get expelled
for this.

262
00:13:47,041 --> 00:13:48,458
Yes, I see.

263
00:13:48,541 --> 00:13:50,666
And that's why you've been
fighting by yourself.

264
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:53,500
So nobody else has
to get in trouble.

265
00:13:57,291 --> 00:14:00,583
Would it be okay
if I told Homura and Miyabi?

266
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,416
[ASUKA]
Sure.

267
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:05,500
I doubt there's any point
in hiding it now.

268
00:14:09,875 --> 00:14:11,500
[YUMI]
Thank you, Asuka.

269
00:14:24,083 --> 00:14:25,958
♪

270
00:14:28,583 --> 00:14:30,458
Do you think they'll come?

271
00:14:30,541 --> 00:14:32,958
Yes. I am quite sure of it.

272
00:14:33,041 --> 00:14:35,375
Now that they're aware
of my true identity,

273
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:37,500
they will have no choice
but to fight.

274
00:14:37,583 --> 00:14:41,000
♪

275
00:14:41,083 --> 00:14:42,500
You see?

276
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:45,208
Listen, Naraku, I'm guessing
that this is gonna be

277
00:14:45,291 --> 00:14:46,708
a pretty long battle.

278
00:14:46,791 --> 00:14:48,500
But no matter what,
you can't get involved, okay.

279
00:14:48,583 --> 00:14:50,333
Yes, I know.

280
00:14:50,416 --> 00:14:52,833
But somehow I doubt
you're going to lose, Kagura.

281
00:14:52,916 --> 00:14:54,500
I'm not terribly concerned.

282
00:14:54,583 --> 00:14:56,958
I appreciate
your vote of confidence.

283
00:14:57,041 --> 00:15:00,000
But I'd say the odds are about
fifty-fifty either way.

284
00:15:00,083 --> 00:15:03,041
♪

285
00:15:03,125 --> 00:15:05,833
I'm impressed you came out here.

286
00:15:05,916 --> 00:15:07,541
Knowing that I'm going
to kill you.

287
00:15:07,625 --> 00:15:09,791
Well, I finally
figured something out.

288
00:15:09,875 --> 00:15:12,041
About why things were off
when we fought before.

289
00:15:12,125 --> 00:15:15,541
It's because you're actually
half youma, aren't you, Fubuki?

290
00:15:15,625 --> 00:15:17,791
Indeed, that's correct.

291
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:23,000
♪

292
00:15:23,083 --> 00:15:24,583
And this is the proof, Kagura.

293
00:15:27,625 --> 00:15:29,916
Looks like
I'll have to kill you, then.

294
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:32,875
[wind whooshing]

295
00:15:32,958 --> 00:15:34,041
[HOMURA]
I get it.

296
00:15:34,125 --> 00:15:36,333
It all makes
a little more sense now.

297
00:15:38,375 --> 00:15:40,791
So why are you telling us this?

298
00:15:40,875 --> 00:15:42,916
It doesn't matter
what the reason is.

299
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,666
The youma are still responsible
for attacking humans,

300
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:47,208
so there's no point
in justifying it

301
00:15:47,291 --> 00:15:49,041
with ridiculous excuses.

302
00:15:49,125 --> 00:15:51,333
Personally, I don't care
who struck first.

303
00:15:52,416 --> 00:15:55,333
I sympathize with Fubuki,
I really do.

304
00:15:55,416 --> 00:15:58,583
But her story isn't
that different from ours.

305
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,250
Like, take the girls
from Gessen,

306
00:16:00,333 --> 00:16:02,333
you've all lost your parents,
as well, right?

307
00:16:02,416 --> 00:16:05,208
Yes, but even so.

308
00:16:05,291 --> 00:16:07,875
I agree with Asuka that we
should seal the youma away,

309
00:16:07,958 --> 00:16:08,833
not kill them.

310
00:16:08,916 --> 00:16:10,666
Well, then count me out.

311
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:13,583
A shinobi's job is
to destroy the youma,

312
00:16:13,666 --> 00:16:15,833
and I refuse
to stray from that.

313
00:16:15,916 --> 00:16:17,625
Now, we're done here.

314
00:16:17,708 --> 00:16:18,916
I'm through talking.

315
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:21,791
[HOMURA]
Poor girl.

316
00:16:21,875 --> 00:16:24,416
Her mother was killed
by a youma, after all.

317
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:25,416
[sighs]

318
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:27,375
I'm not surprised she's mad.

319
00:16:27,458 --> 00:16:28,583
Yeah.

320
00:16:30,291 --> 00:16:32,041
Hey, doesn't not killing
the youma

321
00:16:32,125 --> 00:16:34,208
go against our orders
or whatever?

322
00:16:34,291 --> 00:16:36,458
I mean, we're rogue shinobi,
so we don't care,

323
00:16:36,541 --> 00:16:38,375
but what about
the other students?

324
00:16:41,875 --> 00:16:43,125
A-Asuka?

325
00:16:45,750 --> 00:16:48,500
Even if I'm punished,
I'll still do it.

326
00:16:48,583 --> 00:16:50,291
I've made my choice.

327
00:16:57,250 --> 00:16:58,083
[gasps]

328
00:17:01,583 --> 00:17:04,500
We heard everything
you said in there.

329
00:17:04,583 --> 00:17:06,250
You really are ridiculous.

330
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:08,041
You should have told us, silly!

331
00:17:08,125 --> 00:17:10,583
Besides, we're all
in this together!

332
00:17:10,666 --> 00:17:12,041
Like we always are!

333
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:14,875
And hey, if we get expelled
from Hanzo,

334
00:17:14,958 --> 00:17:16,541
then we'll figure
something else out.

335
00:17:16,625 --> 00:17:18,625
We can be rogue shinobi.

336
00:17:18,708 --> 00:17:20,541
Just like Homura's weird group.

337
00:17:20,625 --> 00:17:23,250
I already have an idea
for a name!

338
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:25,541
"Asuka's Royal Guards"
sounds good, right?

339
00:17:25,625 --> 00:17:27,250
[GIRLS laughing]

340
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:28,666
[IKARUGA]
I actually like it.

341
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:30,541
-Thanks a lot, you guys!
-[HIBARI] Yay!

342
00:17:30,625 --> 00:17:32,458
[ALL laughing]

343
00:17:40,458 --> 00:17:42,333
[ASUKA]
I'll have to do my best.

344
00:17:42,416 --> 00:17:44,458
Because this will be
the last time

345
00:17:44,541 --> 00:17:46,500
I'll be able to fight
alongside them.

346
00:17:50,791 --> 00:17:52,291
[HOMURA]
Fubuki's mother was said to be

347
00:17:52,375 --> 00:17:54,750
the strongest youma
to ever exist.

348
00:17:54,833 --> 00:17:57,666
So which shinobi could have
sealed her away?

349
00:17:57,750 --> 00:17:59,708
Who would be strong enough?

350
00:17:59,791 --> 00:18:02,833
[GIRLS snoring softly]

351
00:18:09,166 --> 00:18:10,166
[YUMI]
Kagura?

352
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:13,583
Sorry to bother you so late.

353
00:18:13,666 --> 00:18:16,625
But I was wondering
if I could have a word with you.

354
00:18:16,708 --> 00:18:17,500
[gasps]

355
00:18:17,583 --> 00:18:19,458
Are you there?

356
00:18:29,541 --> 00:18:31,291
[grunting]

357
00:18:36,083 --> 00:18:37,416
Ah.
[grunts]

358
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:38,333
[gasps]

359
00:18:41,291 --> 00:18:42,333
[KAGURA gasps]

360
00:18:42,416 --> 00:18:43,250
[yells]

361
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:48,875
[BOTH chuckle]

362
00:18:48,958 --> 00:18:53,125
♪

363
00:18:53,208 --> 00:18:54,416
[NARAKU]
Impossible!

364
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:56,250
I didn't think they'd be
on the same level.

365
00:18:58,791 --> 00:19:00,083
[RASETSU]
Please, Fubuki.

366
00:19:00,166 --> 00:19:01,458
You have to win.

367
00:19:01,541 --> 00:19:03,125
For the sake
of our great desire.

368
00:19:03,208 --> 00:19:07,000
♪

369
00:19:07,083 --> 00:19:08,333
[FUBUKI]
What's wrong?

370
00:19:08,416 --> 00:19:10,166
You seem out of breath.

371
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:12,958
[chuckles]
Save your worrying for yourself.

372
00:19:13,041 --> 00:19:14,541
I promise I'm just fine.

373
00:19:14,625 --> 00:19:17,041
[wind whooshing]

374
00:19:17,125 --> 00:19:18,083
[KAGURA]
Now,

375
00:19:18,166 --> 00:19:20,541
what should my next move be?

376
00:19:20,625 --> 00:19:23,791
♪

377
00:19:26,625 --> 00:19:29,583
-[BOTH grunting]
-[weapons clanging]

378
00:19:33,708 --> 00:19:35,000
[grunting]

379
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:41,291
[NARAKU]
Kagura!

380
00:19:41,375 --> 00:19:42,875
Stay there!

381
00:19:42,958 --> 00:19:44,750
You can't interfere, remember?

382
00:19:46,250 --> 00:19:48,625
This fight's gone on
long enough.

383
00:19:48,708 --> 00:19:51,041
Yes. Why don't we end it?

384
00:19:51,125 --> 00:19:55,125
♪

385
00:19:56,458 --> 00:19:58,666
-[wind whooshing]
-[ice clinking]

386
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:01,916
♪

387
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:04,125
Susanowo!

388
00:20:06,166 --> 00:20:07,875
[yelling]

389
00:20:08,916 --> 00:20:10,250
[yelling]

390
00:20:14,041 --> 00:20:17,916
[BOTH yelling]

391
00:20:19,791 --> 00:20:20,958
[YUMI]
Kagura!

392
00:20:21,041 --> 00:20:22,500
[gasps]

393
00:20:22,583 --> 00:20:25,625
Yumi?
What are you doing here?

394
00:20:27,208 --> 00:20:28,041
[groans]

395
00:20:29,041 --> 00:20:30,416
[KAGURA]
I see.

396
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:33,041
I'm not the one who's meant
to finish all this.

397
00:20:33,125 --> 00:20:35,333
So, this is my true destiny?

398
00:20:41,083 --> 00:20:44,125
[groans, screams]

399
00:20:48,666 --> 00:20:50,291
-[NARAKU] Kagura!
-[YUMI] Are you okay?

400
00:20:51,541 --> 00:20:53,416
[NARAKU]
Kagura! Speak to me!

401
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:55,000
[YUMI]
Open your eyes!

402
00:20:55,083 --> 00:20:56,416
-[footsteps approaching]
-[BOTH gasp]

403
00:20:58,166 --> 00:21:00,875
I have decided
that I won't kill you.

404
00:21:00,958 --> 00:21:03,916
I want you to see us destroy
the shinobi.

405
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:06,125
At long last,
justice will prevail.

406
00:21:12,416 --> 00:21:13,750
You're awake!

407
00:21:13,833 --> 00:21:15,375
What happened?

408
00:21:15,458 --> 00:21:17,458
You could have easily won
that fight.

409
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:19,416
[chuckles]

410
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:21,500
Yeah, looks like I messed it up.

411
00:21:21,583 --> 00:21:22,708
Sorry, Naraku.

412
00:21:23,708 --> 00:21:24,750
So now...

413
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:27,333
it's up to you, Yumi.

414
00:21:28,375 --> 00:21:30,916
You'll have to find a way
to stop Fubuki.

415
00:21:32,083 --> 00:21:34,375
But what if I can't do it?

416
00:21:34,458 --> 00:21:35,666
You'll be fine.

417
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:37,000
And I think

418
00:21:37,083 --> 00:21:39,375
you're the only person
who can do it.

419
00:21:39,458 --> 00:21:41,375
Just focus.

420
00:21:41,458 --> 00:21:42,958
Why was she still
carrying around

421
00:21:43,041 --> 00:21:45,625
that accessory
that's the sword and the shield?

422
00:21:45,708 --> 00:21:47,625
You may find an answer there.

423
00:21:47,708 --> 00:21:49,583
♪

424
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:58,375
[whirring, rumbling]

425
00:21:58,458 --> 00:22:00,750
♪

426
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:01,916
[chuckles]

427
00:23:33,750 --> 00:23:36,291
I'm just getting started!

428
00:23:36,375 --> 00:23:38,958
One thing the youma and I
definitely have in common

429
00:23:39,041 --> 00:23:41,125
is how much we adore
super cute girls!

430
00:23:41,208 --> 00:23:42,500
[KATSURAGI]
What's this?

431
00:23:43,750 --> 00:23:45,125
[FUBUKI]
With every passing moment,

432
00:23:45,208 --> 00:23:47,958
my hate only finds a way
to run even deeper!

